<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<pageBreakToken pageId="25" pageNumber="114" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from wet forests of Venezuela (Apure, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bolívar">Bolivar</normalizedToken>
) and Colombia (Meta). Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Distribution of Pachyptera linearis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180451" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">14</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers in January and fruits in April.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes reference to the linear fruit.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="1166580" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180451" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" start="Figure 14" startId="F14">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Figure 14.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="nomenclatural note">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Nomenclatural note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species described here based on new morphological and molecular phylogenetic data (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Schematic diagram summarising phylogenetic relationships within Pachyptera, with morphological characters mapped on the diagram. Names of the terminal taxa indicate the taxon in which these species were previously included. The taxonomic updates proposed here are also indicated. Relationships depicted follow Francisco and Lohmann (submitted)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180438" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">1</figureCitation>
; Francisco and Lohmann submitted). The best quality material was selected as the holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="taxonomic comments">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Taxonomic comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by white and infundibuliform corollas, with a sparsely pubescent and sparsely lepidote ovary. Furthermore, the capsule is linear, flattened, coriaceous to woody, with an inconspicuous longitudinal midline on the valves. The seeds are oblong, thin, coriaceous to woody, winged, with short membranaceous or coriaceous and hyaline wings. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the white infundibuliform flowers with its sister species 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. kerere" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="kerere">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. kerere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Schematic diagram summarising phylogenetic relationships within Pachyptera, with morphological characters mapped on the diagram. Names of the terminal taxa indicate the taxon in which these species were previously included. The taxonomic updates proposed here are also indicated. Relationships depicted follow Francisco and Lohmann (submitted)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180438" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">1</figureCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. linearis" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguible from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. kerere" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="kerere">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. kerere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the fruit morphology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
